name: Amola pizza
address: C5VW+MX2, Penarungan, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1: Nice pizza - had the meatlovers but not just meat - some vegies too.  Crispy crust and spicy fries were great.  Fantastic view of rice fields, friendly staff.  Recommend
review 2: we found this place when we ride home from bedugul. we lost when we heading back, then we found this hidden gem. nice place. good food with affordable price.. enough portion for chix parmigiana. the pizza also good, not thick like PHD but with 40k price this one is great! the spaghetti carbonara also satisfying. the 15k nasi goreng is great. when i read the comment, it says that the chef is work at the hotel before. no wonder the food is yums. this place going to be my fav place to hangout after bedugul.. or when we need peace time.. this place is only 45min from Renon, Denpasar. Unfortunately, we can't find hand soap around the wastafel ðŸ˜… the staff is friendly. if you bring toddler, i think you should really watch them cause this place is next to rice fields. Thanks!
review 3:
A beautiful cozy small cafe in Mengwi area, surrounding by rice field, the view and scenery is just amazing

We tried the Iced Cappuccino, great coffee aroma and the price was affordable
review 4: Cozy little pizza warung with rice fields view. The pizza is very cheap, starting from 30k to 45k. But don't expect the taste and quality to be that of 90k pizza. Such a great place to chill, they provide wifi and playing cards too.
review 5:
Food: good option of pizzas
Location: great view beside ricefield, easy to park with motorbike or car.
Price: not expensive

I like the pizza, nasi goreng is so so. Try to go there afternoon when weather is clear before sunset.

name: Kedai Kayu
address: C5VW+5VX, Penarungan, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
Nice location beside ricefield, price is cheap, easy to find from road, around 30 minutes from city center. They have local snack and local dishes.
Try bubuh bali and kopi bali. Also don't forget es campur to end your day.
review 2: Stopover with good view  and food. There is local food, rujak kuah pinang and Indonesian food.
review 3:
Wow, really tasty tipat kuah. I don't eat much meat and this place is perfect with great choices.
The view is excellent, great atmosphere and even nice local music too.
review 4: Small cafe with amazing sunset and rice field view. Reasonable price, nice food and   friendly owners.

review 1:
Perfect place to spend time with family. You can enjoy view to rice fields while eating.
Or you can choose from big menu everything you want and relax on your way from Kuta to Ubud.
review 2: Very nice place with a fantastic view on the rise field. Good staff can speak English very well and will help you to choose special dish for you. Dont hesitate, its a good place to rest and eat on your way!
